TITLE: Iterating GeoJSON Coordinates using coordEach
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to iterate over coordinates in a GeoJSON FeatureCollection using the coordEach function. Processes each coordinate with access to coordinate index and feature metadata.
SOURCE: https://github.com/turfjs/turf/blob/master/packages/turf-meta/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var features = turf.featureCollection([
  turf.point([26, 37], {"foo": "bar"}),
  turf.point([36, 53], {"hello": "world"})
]);

turf.coordEach(features, function (currentCoord, coordIndex, featureIndex, multiFeatureIndex, geometryIndex) {
  //=currentCoord
  //=coordIndex
  //=featureIndex
  //=multiFeatureIndex
  //=geometryIndex
});
```

