TITLE: Buffering a Point using Turf.js in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to create a buffer around a point using the turf.buffer function. It creates a point at the specified coordinates and then generates a buffer of 500 miles around it.
SOURCE: https://github.com/turfjs/turf/blob/master/packages/turf-buffer/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var point = turf.point([-90.548630, 14.616599]);
var buffered = turf.buffer(point, 500, {units: 'miles'});

//addToMap
var addToMap = [point, buffered]
```

