TITLE: Performing Nearest Neighbor Analysis in JavaScript using Turf.js
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use the nearestNeighborAnalysis function from the @turf/nearest-neighbor-analysis module. It generates random points within a bounding box and performs nearest neighbor analysis on the dataset.
SOURCE: https://github.com/turfjs/turf/blob/master/packages/turf-nearest-neighbor-analysis/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var bbox = [-65, 40, -63, 42];
var dataset = turf.randomPoint(100, { bbox: bbox });
var nearestNeighborStudyArea = turf.nearestNeighborAnalysis(dataset);

//addToMap
var addToMap = [dataset, nearestNeighborStudyArea];
```

