TITLE: Calculating Center Point of GeoJSON Features using Turf.js
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use the turf.center function to calculate the absolute center point of a collection of point features. It also shows how to style the resulting center point for visualization.
SOURCE: https://github.com/turfjs/turf/blob/master/packages/turf-center/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var features = turf.points([
  [-97.522259, 35.4691],
  [-97.502754, 35.463455],
  [-97.508269, 35.463245]
]);

var center = turf.center(features);

//addToMap
var addToMap = [features, center]
center.properties['marker-size'] = 'large';
center.properties['marker-color'] = '#000';
```

