TITLE: Creating Line Segments from Polygon Example - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create 2-vertex line segments from a polygon using the turf.lineSegment function. The example creates a polygon and converts it into line segments that can be added to a map.
SOURCE: https://github.com/turfjs/turf/blob/master/packages/turf-line-segment/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var polygon = turf.polygon([[[-50, 5], [-40, -10], [-50, -10], [-40, 5], [-50, 5]]]);
var segments = turf.lineSegment(polygon);

//addToMap
var addToMap = [polygon, segments]
```

