TITLE: Example Usage of clustersKmeans in Turf.js
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create random points with random z-values and cluster them using the clustersKmeans function with options for specifying the number of clusters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/turfjs/turf/blob/master/packages/turf-clusters-kmeans/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// create random points with random z-values in their properties
var points = turf.randomPoint(100, {bbox: [0, 30, 20, 50]});
var options = {numberOfClusters: 7};
var clustered = turf.clustersKmeans(points, options);

//addToMap
var addToMap = [clustered];
```

