TITLE: Creating Circle Polygons with TurfJS in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Example demonstrating how to create a circle polygon using the turf.circle function. The snippet shows defining a center point, radius, and options with custom steps, units, and properties.
SOURCE: https://github.com/turfjs/turf/blob/master/packages/turf-circle/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var center = [-75.343, 39.984];
var radius = 5;
var options = {steps: 10, units: 'kilometers', properties: {foo: 'bar'}};
var circle = turf.circle(center, radius, options);

//addToMap
var addToMap = [turf.point(center), circle]
```

