TITLE: Smoothing Polygon Example in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to smooth a polygon using the polygonSmooth function with multiple iterations. Creates a polygon and applies smoothing with 3 iterations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/turfjs/turf/blob/master/packages/turf-polygon-smooth/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var polygon = turf.polygon([[[11, 0], [22, 4], [31, 0], [31, 11], [21, 15], [11, 11], [11, 0]]]);

var smoothed = turf.polygonSmooth(polygon, {iterations: 3})

//addToMap
var addToMap = [smoothed, polygon];
```

