TITLE: Using Boolean Contains Function in JavaScript with Turf.js
DESCRIPTION: Example demonstrating how to use the booleanContains function to check if a line contains a point. The function returns true because the point [1, 2] lies on the line.
SOURCE: https://github.com/turfjs/turf/blob/master/packages/turf-boolean-contains/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var line = turf.lineString([[1, 1], [1, 2], [1, 3], [1, 4]]);
var point = turf.point([1, 2]);

turf.booleanContains(line, point);
//=true
```

