TITLE: Creating an Ellipse Polygon using Turf.js
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use the turf.ellipse function to create an ellipse polygon. It specifies a center point, x and y semi-axes, and adds the resulting ellipse to a map along with the center point.
SOURCE: https://github.com/turfjs/turf/blob/master/packages/turf-ellipse/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var center = [-75, 40];
var xSemiAxis = 5;
var ySemiAxis = 2;
var ellipse = turf.ellipse(center, xSemiAxis, ySemiAxis);

//addToMap
var addToMap = [turf.point(center), ellipse]
```

