TITLE: Converting Mercator to WGS84 Projection in JavaScript using Turf.js
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to use the toWgs84 function to convert a Mercator (EPSG:900913) GeoJSON point to WGS84 projection. It creates a point with Mercator coordinates and converts it to WGS84.
SOURCE: https://github.com/turfjs/turf/blob/master/packages/turf-projection/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var pt = turf.point([-7903683.846322424, 5012341.663847514]);
var converted = turf.toWgs84(pt);

//addToMap
var addToMap = [pt, converted];
```

