TITLE: Calculating Polygon Intersection with Turf.js
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to find the intersection between two polygons using the turf.intersect function. The example creates two polygons with specified coordinates and calculates their shared area.
SOURCE: https://github.com/turfjs/turf/blob/master/packages/turf-intersect/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var poly1 = turf.polygon([[
  [-122.801742, 45.48565],
  [-122.801742, 45.60491],
  [-122.584762, 45.60491],
  [-122.584762, 45.48565],
  [-122.801742, 45.48565]
]]);

var poly2 = turf.polygon([[
  [-122.520217, 45.535693],
  [-122.64038, 45.553967],
  [-122.720031, 45.526554],
  [-122.669906, 45.507309],
  [-122.723464, 45.446643],
  [-122.532577, 45.408574],
  [-122.487258, 45.477466],
  [-122.520217, 45.535693]
]]);

var intersection = turf.intersect(turf.featureCollection([poly1, poly2]));

//addToMap
var addToMap = [poly1, poly2, intersection];
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Using truncate function in JavaScript with Turf.js
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use the truncate function from the @turf/truncate module. It creates a point with three coordinates and truncates its precision to 3 decimal places, keeping only 2 coordinates.
SOURCE: https://github.com/turfjs/turf/blob/master/packages/turf-truncate/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

